               <interp inst="t17710911-64-person733" type="surname" value="Davis"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17710911-64-person733" type="given" value="Henry"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17710911-64-person733" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            , of this parish, to write to his ' son, Sir 
               <persName id="t17710911-64-person734">
                  Andrew
                   Chadwick
               <interp inst="t17710911-64-person734" type="surname" value="Chadwick"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17710911-64-person734" type="given" value="Andrew"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17710911-64-person734" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            , of Golden-square, ' London; that it was his desire and will that ' his second son, William, should enjoy his estate, ' at Hasslington, in England; and that after ' his son's death, his children might enjoy the ' same; and that his watch might be given to ' his son Thomas.</p>
               <p>' June 3, 1725.'</p>
               <p>Second.</p>
               <p>' 
               <persName id="t17710911-64-person735">
                  Ellis
                   Chadwick
               <interp inst="t17710911-64-person735" type="surname" value="Chadwick"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17710911-64-person735" type="given" value="Ellis"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17710911-64-person735" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            , and 
               <persName id="t17710911-64-person736">
                  Ann
                   Maria Newmarch
               <interp inst="t17710911-64-person736" type="surname" value="Maria Newmarch"></interp>
